{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Delete selected tracks with safety: \u8226 ? If ALL selected tracks are empty (no items, no automation/envelope data, no FX inserts, no input FX, no sends/receives) AND none is a folder parent with children, delete immediately with no prompt. \u8226 ? Otherwise (any content, folder parents with children, or FX/routing present), show a detailed summary and ask for confirmation. \u8226 ? Summary includes: selected track count, items, automation tracks, folder parents, total child tracks, FX inserts, input FX, sends, receives. Notes:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab "Automation present" = any track envelope has \u8805 ?1 point OR \u8805 ?1 automation item.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab "Folder parent with children" = a selected track whose next track depth is greater than its own.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Child tracks counting includes all descendants under each selected folder parent (until depth returns to or above the parent's depth).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Master track is ignored by REAPER's CountSelectedTracks().\sa180\par}
}

