{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Context-aware item splitting with unified hover/edit logic via library, but performs the split using the native Action 40757 (Split items at edit cursor) to avoid visual fade artifacts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Priority:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1)\tx360\tab Razor Edit spans \u8594 ? split at time selection, keep overlapped items selected, clear razor visuals.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2)\tx360\tab Time Selection (with selected items) \u8594 ? split, then unselect all\u65288 ?\u21487 ?\u22312 ? USER OPTIONS \u35373 ?\u23450 ?\u24573 ?\u30053 ?\u65289 ?.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3)\tx360\tab Hover/Edit path:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab True Hover (mouse over arrange, not Ruler/TCP): \u8226 ? If there are selected items, split those crossing the mouse time; additionally, if the item under mouse is OUTSIDE selection but crosses the time, split it too. \u8226 ? If there is no selection, split the item strictly under the mouse.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Non-hover (Ruler/TCP or Hover OFF): Split items crossing Edit Cursor on selected tracks (fallback).\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Selection policy: \u8226 ? Original selection is preserved. If a previously-selected item is split, BOTH resulting halves remain selected.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Library path: REAPER/Scripts/hsuanice Scripts/Library/hsuanice_Hover.lua\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Debug: \u8226 ? Toggle in USER OPTIONS: DEBUG = true/false \u8226 ? Output \u8594 ? ReaScript console (View \u8594 ? Show console output).\par}
}

