{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Pro Tools-Style Counter Field and Jump to Time\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Mimics Pro Tools' Main Counter Field behavior with cycling numeric input.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-detects project time format (Timecode/Time/Samples/Beat)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Cycling input: when digits exceed max length, automatically wraps to first position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-formats as you type (e.g., 00595800 \u8594 ? 00:59:58:00)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No need to type separators (: or .)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Supports multiple time formats based on project settings\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Supported Formats\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Hours:Minutes:Seconds:Frames (HH:MM:SS:FF) - 8 digits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Minutes:Seconds (MM:SS.mmm) - 7 digits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Measures.Beats.Hundredths (MMM.BB.hh) - 7 digits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Measures.Beats (MMM.BB) - 5 digits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Seconds (sss.mmm) - variable length\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Samples - variable length\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Absolute Frames - variable length\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Run script to open the Counter window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Type numbers continuously (no separators needed)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Press Enter to navigate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Press + for relative forward offset (e.g., +01000000 = +1 hour from current)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Press - for relative backward offset (e.g., -00300000 = -30 minutes from current)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Press \u9003 ? (Backspace) or \u8998 ? (Delete) to clear input\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab Press / or numpad Clear to reset to zero (00:00:00:00)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Press = to reset to current timeline position\sa180\par}
}

